and have a good time."

01:33.633 --> 01:35.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And he added, "So sad."

01:35.700 --> 01:39.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Trump had urged the Obama
administration to veto the
Israel resolution, instead of

01:39.700 --> 01:41.667 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
abstaining.

01:41.667 --> 01:44.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This has been a day of mourning
in Russia for the victims
of a military plane crash

01:44.967 --> 01:47.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that killed 92 people.

01:47.500 --> 01:50.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The plane went down Sunday
morning, just minutes
after taking off from
the southern city of

01:50.933 --> 01:53.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Sochi, en route to Syria.

01:53.033 --> 01:57.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, divers pulled fragments
of the plane out of the Black
Sea, and a massive search

01:57.167 --> 02:01.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
operation continued
as investigators
searched for a cause.

02:01.733 --> 02:06.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MAXIM SOKOLOV, Russian
Transportation Minister
(through translator):
As we know, the main

02:08.067 --> 02:10.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
causes so far do not
include an act of terrorism.

02:10.033 --> 02:14.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we think that the reason for
the crash could be a technical
fault or a pilot error,

02:14.333 --> 02:19.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but I repeat it will
be clarified by the
investigation of a Ministry
of Defense special technical

02:19.233 --> 02:21.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
commission.

02:21.300 --> 02:24.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The Russian
intelligence agency FSB said
today it has found no signs

02:24.467 --> 02:27.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
pointing to sabotage
or terror in the crash.

02:27.733 --> 02:32.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Syria, Russian troops
say they have uncovered
mass graves in Eastern
Aleppo since its recapture

02:33.333 --> 02:35.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from rebels.

02:35.333 --> 02:38.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Defense Ministry said
today that several dozen bodies
were found, victims of torture

02:38.600 --> 02:40.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and mutilation.

02:40.600 --> 02:43.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Russians sent military
police into Eastern Aleppo after
helping the Syrian government

02:43.633 --> 02:45.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
retake the city.

02:45.733 --> 02:50.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there's word that China's
1st Aircraft Carrier Group has
sailed past Taiwan and into

02:50.233 --> 02:52.367 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the contested South China Sea.

02:52.367 --> 02:56.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Chinese warships passed
islands controlled by
Taiwan in a show of force.

02:56.600 --> 03:01.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Beijing says it's a routine
exercise, but it comes amid
rising tensions over Taiwan's

03:02.067 --> 03:04.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
status.

03:04.633 --> 03:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Philippines faced
widespread power outages
and evacuations today,
after a powerful Christmas

03:08.633 --> 03:10.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
typhoon.

03:10.700 --> 03:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Typhoon Nock-ten made landfall
overnight, killing six people
and forced nearly 400,000

03:14.400 --> 03:16.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to flee.

03:16.400 --> 03:20.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Five provinces lost power
completely as winds of more than
100 miles an hour tore through

03:20.600 --> 03:22.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
power lines and damaged homes.

03:22.633 --> 03:26.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator):
The water from the streets
became so strong, it came into

03:26.367 --> 03:28.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our house.

03:28.433 --> 03:31.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): I
told my family to evacuate and
leave our belongings behind.

03:31.433 --> 03:33.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We needed to save
our lives first.

03:33.900 --> 03:38.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The
typhoon disrupted Christmas
celebrations in Asia's
largest Catholic nation,

03:39.100 --> 03:41.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and stranded some 12,000
holiday travelers.

03:41.300 --> 03:45.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Blizzard conditions in
the Dakotas kept major
highways closed today
and knocked out power

03:45.267 --> 03:47.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
through Nebraska and Iowa.

03:47.233 --> 03:51.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Heavy snow, ice and winds
moved in over the Christmas
weekend, forcing authorities to

03:51.700 --> 03:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
post several no-travel warnings.

03:54.100 --> 03:58.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Forecasters expect the
storm to move into the
Northeast later in the week.

03:58.367 --> 04:02.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
