take much of a holiday break.

04:26.033 --> 04:30.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From the ongoing turf war
between outgoing President Obama
and soon-to-be President Trump

04:30.800 --> 04:34.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to a new pledge this weekend to
dissolve the Trump Foundation
over possible conflicts of

04:34.733 --> 04:38.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
interest, there's plenty to
talk about this Politics Monday.

04:38.200 --> 04:43.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Joining me are Amy Walter of
The Cook Political Report and
Stu Rothenberg of The Rothenberg

04:43.033 --> 04:45.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
&amp; Gonzales Political Report.

04:45.533 --> 04:47.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to you both.

04:47.600 --> 04:51.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have seen, over this weekend,
and in the past week or so,
president-elect Trump inserting

04:53.700 --> 04:57.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
himself very overtly into
American policy on Israel,
on Taiwan and China.

04:58.867 --> 05:00.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He's negotiating
government contracts.

05:00.800 --> 05:04.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm curious, Amy, is this as
unprecedented as it seems?

05:04.933 --> 05:07.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY WALTER, The Cook Political
Report: It is unprecedented.

05:07.033 --> 05:11.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we, of course, have never
had a president-elect coming
in the age of Twitter either.

05:11.033 --> 05:13.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So there's that piece of it.

05:13.300 --> 05:17.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I feel like a broken
record, but every time we're
together, I say the same thing,

05:17.867 --> 05:22.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which is we have to expect
that this is going to be an
unprecedented presidency.

05:22.600 --> 05:25.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He ran an unprecedented
kind of campaign.

05:25.067 --> 05:29.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's been showing no
signs of being a different
president-elect than
he was as a candidate.

05:29.200 --> 05:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I think he's also showing
us the kind of president that
he's going to be, especially

05:33.133 --> 05:38.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on an issue like Israel, where
he's going to move much closer
to where the hard-liners,

05:40.000 --> 05:44.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
especially Benjamin
Netanyahu, want the U.S. to
be than where Obama was.

05:46.500 --> 05:48.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a relationship between
Israel and the U.S. during
the Obama years that hasn't

05:48.833 --> 05:51.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
exactly been the
nicest and friendliest.

05:51.433 --> 05:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Stu, is that
your take as well, that this
is just the way it's going

05:54.200 --> 05:56.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to be?

05:56.233 --> 05:58.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUART ROTHENBERG, Editor and
Publisher, The Rothenberg &amp;
Gonzales Political Report: Yes,

05:58.200 --> 06:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it's a man with huge
personality and a huge
ego with lots of opinions.

06:00.200 --> 06:04.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And unlike traditional
politicians, all of our previous
presidents, he has a different

06:05.100 --> 06:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
kind of filter or no filter.

06:07.200 --> 06:11.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he thinks that, when he has
an opinion, he should offer it
and people would be interested.

06:11.600 --> 06:12.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And they are interested.

06:12.667 --> 06:14.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I agree with Amy entirely.

06:14.733 --> 06:18.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would expect this throughout
the presidency, at least over
the next couple of years, where

06:18.700 --> 06:23.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he likes to interject himself,
solve problems, make points,
and he will continue to do that.

06:25.767 --> 06:29.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMY WALTER: And, look, there
is not really a distinctive
line between foreign policy

06:29.667 --> 06:34.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and other policies, right,
that when you're negotiating
trade, you can also negotiate

06:36.667 --> 06:38.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
foreign policy and defense
contracts and where our
warships are positioned.

06:38.933 --> 06:41.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's all part
of a big package.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUART ROTHENBERG: And in terms
of the language - - just want
to point, just in terms of the

06:43.067 --> 06:46.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
language, while politicians
use diplomatic language and
they are very concerned about

06:46.467 --> 06:50.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the words they use and the
phrases, Donald Trump is never
concerned about a particular

06:50.400 --> 06:52.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
word or phrase.

06:52.433 --> 06:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He wants to get a point across
and he says it bluntly if
he wants to, and he usually

06:56.133 --> 06:58.167 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
wants to.

06:58.167 --> 07:00.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Do you think
in the end, though, any of
this really affects policy?

07:00.167 --> 07:04.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I understand the appearance
of having an armchair
president in waiting.

07:04.133 --> 07:06.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Does it change policy
in any substantive way?

07:06.067 --> 07:09.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY WALTER: It will when he's
no longer the president-elect.

07:09.300 --> 07:12.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And so that's really
the question that we're
all waiting to see.

07:12.100 --> 07:15.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Right now, he sends out
his opinions, his tweets.

07:15.133 --> 07:19.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We see sometimes there is a
reaction, but nothing that has
been particularly substantive,

07:19.733 --> 07:22.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in part because we have
one president right now.

07:22.533 --> 07:27.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When he becomes the president
and he sends a tweet out, and
let's say warships move based

07:28.967 --> 07:32.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on that tweet, then we will have
a very different conversation.

07:32.067 --> 07:36.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Unless and until that happens,
though, we have to just sort
of expect that this is the

07:36.367 --> 07:38.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
way he's going to
conduct himself.

07:38.833 --> 07:43.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we're going to learn a lot
more once the people he has
hired, secretary of defense,

07:45.833 --> 07:50.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
secretary of state, how they
perform and whether they have a
greater influence on policy, but

07:51.367 --> 07:53.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
also on his behavior.

07:53.433 --> 07:57.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUART ROTHENBERG: I would
say, for the near term, those
of us who read the tweets and

07:57.233 --> 08:02.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
