So it takes, at least in the
short-term, this political
headache, right, well, only just

09:30.467 --> 09:31.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
giving me bad problems.

09:31.900 --> 09:33.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's not a particularly
large foundation.

09:33.867 --> 09:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, it takes that off the table.

09:36.200 --> 09:39.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Also gives him the opportunity
to say, hey, look, unlike the
Clintons, when it looks like

09:39.900 --> 09:44.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
something could be pay for
play or there is a problem
with my foundation, I will just

09:44.133 --> 09:49.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
close it down, rather than
making it -- or raising these
questions about conflicts.

09:51.033 --> 09:53.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But to Stu's point, there
are still too many other
conflicts that are out there.

09:53.833 --> 09:57.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the question is, ultimately,
we know that reporters are
going to be interested in this

09:57.833 --> 09:59.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and tracking this
down consistently.

09:59.933 --> 10:04.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How focused will voters be on
this and how long will they
see each and every one of his

10:05.933 --> 10:08.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
decisions impacting
his business?

10:08.200 --> 10:11.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That
always does seem to be
the ongoing question.

10:11.433 --> 10:15.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The AP, Lisa Lerer, had a really
interesting piece looking at
several of the things that

10:15.733 --> 10:20.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump criticized Hillary
Clinton for during the campaign
that he is now himself doing,

10:22.700 --> 10:25.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things like having a lot of
members of Goldman Sachs in his
inner circle, not having press

10:25.833 --> 10:27.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
conferences, things like that.

10:27.500 --> 10:31.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Do you think that those
matter to voters, to
his constituency at all?

10:31.933 --> 10:36.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUART ROTHENBERG: I don't
think they matter to Trump
voters, Trump supporters.

10:36.633 --> 10:41.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No, because I think they can
explain that away, it's the
media, it's misstatements by

10:42.833 --> 10:44.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
opponents, it's
liberal Democrats.

10:44.800 --> 10:46.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So I don't think
that's a problem.

10:46.867 --> 10:50.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With the media, members of
the media will continue to be
interested in that, and will

10:52.567 --> 10:54.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
continue to ask, when
are you going to have
a press conference?

10:54.333 --> 10:57.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But to Trump supporters, no,
I don't think it's a big deal.

10:57.033 --> 10:59.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AMY WALTER: Yes.

10:59.200 --> 11:02.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I was sitting in a
focus group with voters
last week in Ohio who
had all supported Donald

11:02.733 --> 11:03.967 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Trump.

11:03.967 --> 11:06.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Now, they weren't all
hard, solid Republicans.

11:06.033 --> 11:08.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Many of them had voted for Obama
or Bill Clinton in the past.

11:08.900 --> 11:12.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But when you asked the question
about conflict of interest,
their answer, the way that they

11:12.833 --> 11:17.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
helped to process this is
they said, look, he comes in
already very rich, so he can't

11:18.700 --> 11:20.167 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be bought off.

11:20.167 --> 11:22.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And you heard that a lot
on the campaign trail, too.

11:22.233 --> 11:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What they were frustrated
about with Hillary Clinton and
other traditional politicians

11:26.233 --> 11:30.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was that they came to Washington
and then got rich, as opposed
to they are already rich

11:30.300 --> 11:32.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
when they came to
Washington, so of course
you can't be corrupted.

11:32.500 --> 11:33.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: He's
inoculated from it.

11:33.500 --> 11:35.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AMY WALTER: Right.

11:35.567 --> 11:37.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can't be corrupted if you
already have all this money
and you are not looking for

11:37.067 --> 11:38.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the money.

11:38.067 --> 11:39.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We will see.

11:39.067 --> 11:41.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will see how long it lasts.

11:41.133 --> 11:45.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Again, it's great in theory,
but to Stu's point, once it's
January 20, and you're president

11:47.100 --> 11:50.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the United States and you're
making decisions, the lines are
going to get much darker and

11:51.567 --> 11:53.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
much clearer.

11:53.700 --> 11:57.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
Amy Walter, Stu Rothenberg,
thank you both very much.

11:58.867 --> 12:02.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
STUART ROTHENBERG: Thank you.

12:02.100 --> 12:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: You're very welcome.

12:06.133 --> 12:11.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Eighteen
months into Europe's
refugee crisis, tension
has surfaced on the

12:12.567 --> 12:14.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Greek island of Lesbos.

12:14.567 --> 12:18.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It wasn't so long ago that the
islanders were being considered
for the Nobel Peace Prize

12:18.333 --> 12:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for their welcoming of refugees.

12:20.500 --> 12:25.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But income from tourism,
on which many islanders
depend, has plummeted
this year, and hostility

12:25.233 --> 12:29.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
towards refugees and to
the volunteers helping
them has only grown.

12:29.333 --> 12:32.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
From Lesbos, special
correspondent Malcolm
Brabant reports.

12:32.600 --> 12:37.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Skala
Sikaminia, Skala Sikaminia,
a small fishing village
in northern Lesbos,

12:37.433 --> 12:42.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the tranquil dawn is about
to get busy.

12:47.433 --> 12:52.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The first raft of the
day has been spotted
about five miles away.

12:54.467 --> 12:59.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Volunteers from Refugee
Rescue, an Irish charity,
are scrambling to help.

13:01.367 --> 13:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The raft is intercepted by a
coast guard cutter after leaving
Turkey's shore and entering

13:05.500 --> 13:06.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Greek waters.

13:06.500 --> 13:08.567 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REV.

13:08.567 --> 13:10.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FATHER CHRISTOFOROS SCHUFF,
Lesbos: When it comes to the
fact that many of these people

13:10.267 --> 13:14.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
arriving are Muslims, we are
supposed to love everyone.

13:14.033 --> 13:18.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Waiting
for them is Californian
orthodox priest father
Christoforos, who has

13:18.867 --> 13:20.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
lived in Lesbos for 15 years.

13:20.933 --> 13:25.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At a time when Europe
is becoming increasingly
anxious about the influx
of Muslim refugees

13:27.233 --> 13:30.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and economic migrants,
Christoforos doesn't
waver from his creed.

13:30.033 --> 13:32.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REV.

13:32.100 --> 13:33.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FATHER CHRISTOFOROS SCHUFF:
Theologically, we are supposed
to see every human being as

13:33.367 --> 13:35.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
God.

13:35.700 --> 13:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And how we treat that
person is how we treat God.

13:39.733 --> 13:42.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This a sacred ideal
to love the foreigner.

13:42.867 --> 13:46.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It is the exact
opposite of xenophobia.

13:46.033 --> 13:48.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is something
which is sacred.

13:48.500 --> 13:53.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Mission
accomplished, 55 souls saved,
including 15 women and seven

13:56.867 --> 14:00.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
children, most from
sub-Saharan Africa.

14:00.700 --> 14:05.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: I thank God I'm here.

14:10.667 --> 14:15.667 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm so afraid.

14:15.667 --> 14:20.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: We spent like four hours
to reach Greece territory.

14:32.333 --> 14:36.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Right now, I'm feeling cold.

14:36.267 --> 14:37.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Right now,
I'm feeling cold.

14:37.267 --> 14:38.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm not feeling right now.

14:38.500 --> 14:39.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOMAN: I'm feeling proud
of the people I meet.

14:39.300 --> 14:40.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm proud of them.

14:40.267 --> 14:41.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Thank you plenty, plenty.

14:41.267 --> 14:44.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: My life is in danger.

14:44.533 --> 14:47.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's why I come here.

14:47.733 --> 14:50.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My life is at risk.

14:50.933 --> 14:54.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm running for my life.

14:54.133 --> 14:56.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: You warming up now?

14:56.433 --> 15:00.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will get you in 10 minutes.

15:00.133 --> 15:04.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We will get you into
the camp and you will
get some dry clothes.

15:04.667 --> 15:05.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT:
Where are you from?

15:05.933 --> 15:07.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Comoros.

15:07.133 --> 15:08.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT:
The Comoros Islands?

15:08.767 --> 15:10.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: Yes, Comoros Island.

15:10.067 --> 15:11.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But
that's a paradise.

15:11.400 --> 15:12.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Yes.

15:12.833 --> 15:16.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Why
have you left a paradise?

15:16.733 --> 15:20.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: It is a paradise,
but it's very poor.

15:20.267 --> 15:22.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's very poor.

15:22.800 --> 15:27.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Like most
other Greek communities,
Skala Sikaminia has
endured seven years of

15:28.967 --> 15:33.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
economic hardship, but
the selflessness of
the Nobel-nominated
villagers is one of the

15:33.133 --> 15:36.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
reasons why Refugee
Rescue is based here.

15:36.500 --> 15:38.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Coordinator Baz Fischer.

15:38.600 --> 15:42.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BAZ FISCHER, Refugee Rescue:
There have been tensions in
other places, definitely.

15:42.467 --> 15:45.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And if we can, we'd always
like to bring them here.

15:45.867 --> 15:50.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If every village down the
coast was like here, it would
make things a lot easier.

15:52.867 --> 15:57.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: This footage
was shot by activists at the
nearby port of Petra in the

15:59.467 --> 16:03.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
summer, as local people
blockaded the jetty
in an attempt to stop
the coast guard from

16:03.700 --> 16:07.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
transferring refugees in front
of their tourist beaches.

16:07.633 --> 16:12.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As a result of alleged
intimidation, including
vandalism of their
vehicles, volunteer groups

16:13.700 --> 16:16.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
avoid Petra and Molyvos
five miles away.

16:16.033 --> 16:21.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With its magnificent 15th
century citadel, Molyvos is the
architectural jewel of Lesbos

16:22.233 --> 16:24.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and is almost entirely
dependent on tourism.

16:24.433 --> 16:28.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But according to Mayor
Athanasios Andriotis,
income was down by 70
percent this year, as

16:30.267 --> 16:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
vacationers stayed away
because of the refugee crisis.

16:33.200 --> 16:35.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He acknowledged there
was some tension.

16:35.800 --> 16:38.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ATHANASIOS ANDRIOTIS,
Mayor of Molyvos (through
translator): The people
are annoyed and worried

16:38.800 --> 16:42.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
about the future because
this situation seems to
be becoming permanent.

16:42.233 --> 16:46.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's one which is no good
for the people of Molyvos, nor,
unfortunately, for the refugee

16:46.833 --> 16:48.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
migrants who come here.

16:48.833 --> 16:51.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: There are some
people who say that the coast
guard has not been allowed

16:51.267 --> 16:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to drop people in Molyvos
because there is such hostility.

16:54.200 --> 16:57.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ATHANASIOS ANDRIOTIS (through
translator): The figures
here for tourism have dropped

16:57.667 --> 17:00.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to almost zero because
of the refugee issue.

17:00.267 --> 17:02.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This can't go on.

17:02.367 --> 17:05.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have to understand that,
OK, they have arrived here,
but they have to go somewhere

17:05.267 --> 17:07.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
else more secluded to disembark.

17:07.300 --> 17:11.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The consequence
is that it takes longer for
the coast guard or volunteers

17:11.700 --> 17:15.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to take migrants to ports
where they will be accepted.

17:15.033 --> 17:20.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This angers British
volunteer and Lesbos
resident Eric Kempson, who
we first met 18 months ago

17:21.433 --> 17:23.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and have since encountered
on several occasions.

17:23.967 --> 17:28.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He and his family have
repeatedly been threatened
because of his outspoken
pro-refugee stance.

17:29.667 --> 17:30.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ERIC KEMPSON, Volunteer:
This is very dangerous.

17:30.600 --> 17:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We are going to lose people.

17:33.133 --> 17:36.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You could see, it took
so long to come here,
and they're sitting on
the boat, they're soaking

17:36.967 --> 17:38.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
wet, they're freezing cold.

17:38.200 --> 17:40.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The temperature
is close to zero.

17:40.167 --> 17:44.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you have a few people
holding two towns to ransom
because they don't want refugees

17:46.500 --> 17:49.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
in there, this is
absolutely disgusting,
absolutely disgusting.

17:49.367 --> 17:52.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
People are going to die
here this winter because
of these few people.

17:52.600 --> 17:57.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Dimitris
Drakolias has been on
the receiving end of
anti-migrant hostility.

17:57.267 --> 18:00.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He runs a hotel in the
small resort of Petra.

18:00.267 --> 18:05.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Local hard-liners
blockaded the village and
whipped up an Internet
campaign after he agreed

18:06.867 --> 18:08.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to provide temporary
accommodation for
22 refugee children.

18:08.933 --> 18:13.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DIMITRIS DRAKOLIAS, Hotelier:
People got afraid that we were
supposed to bring refugees here

18:14.500 --> 18:16.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and stay for three --
two, three, four months.

18:16.733 --> 18:19.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's a very
uncomfortable situation.

18:19.767 --> 18:24.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nobody came up to me and do
anything, but I can understand
that they didn't like that

18:26.733 --> 18:29.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that I hosted 20 kids
inside the hotel.

18:29.767 --> 18:33.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Did
you feel intimidated?

18:33.033 --> 18:35.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DIMITRIS DRAKOLIAS:
A little bit.

18:35.400 --> 18:38.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
A little bit.

18:38.033 --> 18:39.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The
hotelier says the Internet
campaign was orchestrated
by a tourist organization

18:39.333 --> 18:41.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
called The Other Aegean.

18:41.500 --> 18:45.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We arranged an interview
with The Other Aegean's
chairman, Nikos Molvalis
(ph), who only wanted

18:45.967 --> 18:50.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to discuss the tourist
industry's 70 percent
losses and other problems.

18:50.800 --> 18:55.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have been talking to the
owner of the Clara Hotel, who
says that your organization was

18:55.167 --> 19:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
responsible for blockading
the place to make sure that
refugees didn't turn up there.

19:01.067 --> 19:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Can you explain that, please?

19:02.300 --> 19:05.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOMAN: He doesn't want
to talk about that.

19:05.033 --> 19:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Why don't
you want to talk about that?

19:07.733 --> 19:10.167 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Because he's already
answered the question.

19:10.167 --> 19:12.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT:
Off-camera, Molvalis
claimed to have intervened
on behalf of the refugee

19:12.667 --> 19:14.167 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
children.

19:14.167 --> 19:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Otherwise, he said there
would have been bloodshed.

19:15.100 --> 19:16.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REV.

19:16.533 --> 19:19.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FATHER CHRISTOFOROS
SCHUFF: This is not true.

19:19.067 --> 19:21.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The
tension troubles Father
Christoforos, who believes
some of the volunteers

19:21.900 --> 19:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
don't fully understand the
plight of the islanders.

19:24.533 --> 19:26.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REV.

19:26.033 --> 19:27.267 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
FATHER CHRISTOFOROS SCHUFF:
I see people are affected.

19:27.267 --> 19:29.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I understand why
they are affected.

19:29.267 --> 19:33.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Their pocketbooks hurting
and they want to find
somewhere to put the blame.

19:33.500 --> 19:38.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But at the same time, a lot
of these same people will not
only blame the refugees or

19:40.500 --> 19:44.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the organizations, but they
also blame the government just
as much for not doing more.

19:46.000 --> 19:49.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The numbers of
people arriving on the islands
are just a fraction of the

19:51.400 --> 19:55.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
thousands that were
landing daily when the
crisis was at its peak.

19:55.800 --> 20:00.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there is a steady trickle,
and, slowly, slowly, the
islands are filling up again.

20:00.000 --> 20:03.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's a serious shortage of
accommodation for these people.

20:03.400 --> 20:08.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there's genuine concern
here that Europe's deal with
Turkey will break down, and once

20:08.233 --> 20:13.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
again the islands
will be inundated with
refugees and migrants.

20:15.200 --> 20:18.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The influx increases
the pressure in Moria,
the overcrowded and
tense camp in the south

20:18.233 --> 20:22.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the island visited by the
pope earlier in the year.

20:22.500 --> 20:27.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Frustrated migrants, angry
at conditions and the time it
takes to process asylum claims,

20:28.667 --> 20:31.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
have, on occasions, set
fires inside the camp.

20:31.933 --> 20:36.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A Muslim charity has established
a feeding station just outside
Moria, claiming the camp

20:38.033 --> 20:39.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
caterers are cheating
the residents.

20:39.700 --> 20:43.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MAN: Food in Moria, they
recook it three times,
two to three times.

20:43.633 --> 20:44.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is what they say.

20:44.767 --> 20:45.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not eatable.

20:45.833 --> 20:47.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And they say it's dirty.

20:47.567 --> 20:48.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: Moria, no good.

20:48.767 --> 20:49.767 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Here, good.

20:49.767 --> 20:51.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We want freedom.

20:51.400 --> 20:54.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Here, the food delicious,
and Moria not delicious.

20:54.433 --> 20:56.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: Moria is like a jail.

20:56.400 --> 20:58.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Not good.

20:58.700 --> 21:03.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the situation is really
bad, really a lot of problems,
calls -- every day fight,

21:04.600 --> 21:05.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
every night fight.

21:05.600 --> 21:06.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Fire.

21:06.600 --> 21:07.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Fight.

21:07.600 --> 21:08.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Fire.

21:08.600 --> 21:10.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
A lot of problems.

21:10.100 --> 21:12.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Not everyone
is enduring spartan conditions.

21:12.633 --> 21:17.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Along with 200 other vulnerable
people, five members of the
Nikzad family are living in

21:19.100 --> 21:22.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a holiday hotel run by the
Catholic charity Caritas.

21:22.100 --> 21:27.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Sahil is desperately
missing regular school.

21:28.500 --> 21:31.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But in three months, he has
made good progress with English.

21:31.000 --> 21:35.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAHIL NIKZAD, Refugee:
In Afghanistan, the
Taliban, I can't go to
school because explosions,

21:38.733 --> 21:41.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a bomb.

21:41.333 --> 21:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We want to go to some
good place, good country,
because,there, we learned
-- we go to school.

21:50.400 --> 21:53.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have a good home.

21:53.000 --> 21:57.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Every
new arrival who survives
the perilous crossing
shares the same ambition.

21:59.067 --> 22:02.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
As the numbers mount, their
chances of success diminish.

22:02.400 --> 22:07.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The warm welcome of Skala
Sikaminia goes cold as soon
as they leave the village.

22:07.367 --> 22:12.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The buzzword in Europe is
deportation, especially
after an Islamist
terrorist used a truck to

22:13.367 --> 22:16.167 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
kill 12 people in Berlin.

22:16.167 --> 22:20.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This year, more migrants than
ever before died trying to
cross the Mediterranean to

22:20.833 --> 22:21.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Europe.

22:21.833 --> 22:24.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Yet still they come.

22:24.067 --> 22:28.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Father Christoforos may be a
lighthouse, but much of Europe
wishes that his beam would

22:28.833 --> 22:30.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be extinguished.

22:30.333 --> 22:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Malcolm Brabant in Lesbos.

22:37.067 --> 22:42.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Stay with us.

22:46.367 --> 22:50.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
the legacy of pop star George
Michael; a conversation with

22:50.733 --> 22:55.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Israel's best-known novelist;
and a saxophonist describes what
he calls the music of freedom

22:56.367 --> 22:58.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and wonder.

22:58.100 --> 23:01.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But first: It was yet
another bloody holiday
weekend in Chicago.

23:01.633 --> 23:06.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Five more people were shot
this morning, bringing the toll
since Friday afternoon to nearly

23:06.100 --> 23:08.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
50.

23:08.100 --> 23:12.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Eleven people were killed,
and Chicago is now set to
pass 700 homicides this year.

23:13.533 --> 23:15.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's a level not seen
there since the late '90s.

23:15.667 --> 23:19.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Police said much of the violence
was clustered in areas with
historical gang problems on

23:19.467 --> 23:21.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the South and West Sides.

23:21.433 --> 23:25.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And police Superintendent
Eddie Johnson said at a news
conference today that the nature

23:25.400 --> 23:27.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of those disputes is changing.

23:27.100 --> 23:30.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
EDDIE JOHNSON, Chicago
Police Superintendent:
Here's the bottom line.

23:30.167 --> 23:35.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, with the technology we have
in place, social media drives
a lot of our gang disputes.

23:37.133 --> 23:38.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're on Facebook, on
Instagram, on Twitter
disrespecting each other.

23:38.233 --> 23:40.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They will live-stream
disrespects.

23:40.267 --> 23:42.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when they do that, they
go out there and look for
them, and they get them.

23:46.267 --> 23:48.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So it's not just drugs anymore.

23:48.067 --> 23:50.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's petty disputes.

23:50.000 --> 23:53.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That
problem was one of several big
challenges that the "NewsHour"'s

23:53.633 --> 23:56.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
John Yang heard about
when he reported there
earlier this summer.

23:56.800 --> 23:59.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He also examined what is
being done to combat it.

23:59.300 --> 24:04.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For some context, back
then, there were roughly
200 fewer homicides in
Chicago at that time.

24:05.433 --> 24:07.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Here's a second
look at his report.

24:07.600 --> 24:12.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: On this busy street
corner in Englewood, one of the
hardest-hit neighborhoods on the

24:14.633 --> 24:17.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
city's troubled South Side,
it looks like a party.

24:17.467 --> 24:19.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Kids are playing.

24:19.367 --> 24:22.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The grill is fired up.

24:22.533 --> 24:24.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In the past, though, 75th and
Stewart felt like a war zone.

24:24.433 --> 24:27.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TAMAR MANASSEH, Mothers Against
Senseless Killings: This
corner is a corner where a

24:27.833 --> 24:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
man was killed -- well,
several men, a woman was
killed, and a child was killed.

24:34.833 --> 24:38.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A 9-year-old girl was killed
right across the street over
there washing her dog in broad

24:38.100 --> 24:40.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
daylight.

24:40.133 --> 24:44.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: But for two summers,
a group called Mothers Against
Senseless Killings, or MASK,

24:46.100 --> 24:49.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
led by Tamar Manasseh, has been
out on this corner, and there
hasn't been a single shooting.

24:52.000 --> 24:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Volunteer Laura Lambert (ph)
comes from nearby Hyde Park.

24:55.133 --> 25:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And 91-year-old Edwina Knight
(ph) crosses the street every
day from the house she's

25:00.933 --> 25:02.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
lived in for 57 years.

25:02.133 --> 25:04.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TAMAR MANASSEH: Just show up.

25:04.233 --> 25:06.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's all you have to do.

25:06.267 --> 25:08.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Show up, grab a lawn chair
and a pair of sunglasses,
and you can do this.

25:08.967 --> 25:11.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You can change the
world with that.

25:11.033 --> 25:15.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: But the moms of
MASK are only on one corner in
a city of 2.7 million people.

25:18.133 --> 25:20.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Killings have
spiked this summer.

25:20.567 --> 25:25.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Chicago has already recorded
more homicides this year than
it did in all of last year.

25:25.233 --> 25:27.767 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

25:27.767 --> 25:29.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GARY SLUTKIN, University
of Illinois at Chicago:
This is also very
typical of all epidemics.

25:29.000 --> 25:31.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You can see the high
density of shootings.

25:31.100 --> 25:35.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: University
of Illinois at Chicago
physician Gary Slutkin
says epidemic is exactly

25:36.900 --> 25:38.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the right word.

25:38.433 --> 25:41.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He argues that violence
is a contagious disease.

25:41.633 --> 25:43.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

25:43.600 --> 25:45.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GARY SLUTKIN: For example,
you're exposed to flu, you're
more likely to get flu.

25:45.067 --> 25:47.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You don't actually get
flu without being exposed.

25:47.633 --> 25:50.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Same thing for T.B.,
cholera and violence.

25:50.100 --> 25:54.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, why does someone
who was exposed to child
abuse, abuse their own kids?

25:54.133 --> 25:58.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That would be the person who
you would think would be least
likely to do it, because he

25:58.233 --> 26:00.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
knows how bad it was.

26:00.167 --> 26:02.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, in fact, he's
picked up this contagious
set of behaviors.

26:02.267 --> 26:07.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: So Dr. Slutkin
treats gun violence as
a contagious disease.

26:09.300 --> 26:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He founded Cure Violence, now
an international effort that
trains former gang members and

26:14.000 --> 26:17.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
felons to stop violence in its
tracks, violence interrupters.

26:17.667 --> 26:19.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

26:19.733 --> 26:23.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GARY SLUTKIN: They are always in
the community, aware of what's
going on, and asking families

26:24.833 --> 26:27.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and people, you
know, who's upset?

26:27.267 --> 26:31.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, who is -- somebody
slept with someone's
girlfriend, someone was
disrespected, someone

26:32.333 --> 26:33.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
owes somebody money.

26:33.800 --> 26:36.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we can reach those people
with these health workers.

26:36.633 --> 26:39.167 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They may not look like
health workers to everybody.

26:39.167 --> 26:43.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They know how to cool people
down, know how to buy time,

26:43.333 --> 26:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Chicago violence
interrupter Chico Tillmon
knows how to cool people down.

26:48.233 --> 26:52.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He drove us around the South
Side last week, where much
of the violence happens.

26:52.433 --> 26:56.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHICO TILLMON, Violence
Interrupter: In early January,
two cliques were arguing.

26:56.967 --> 27:01.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So one clique went into another
clique's neighborhood and got on
Facebook Live and was like: F.

27:02.433 --> 27:03.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you all.

27:03.433 --> 27:05.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We're in your all neighbor.

27:05.067 --> 27:07.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We're in your all gas station.

27:07.333 --> 27:12.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Within 30 minutes, on that
walk from the gas station back
to the house, two were dead,

27:14.433 --> 27:15.867 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
one was wounded.

27:15.867 --> 27:19.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN YANG: It's not like
this is a gang war over turf.

27:19.933 --> 27:21.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is just sort of...

27:21.133 --> 27:23.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHICO TILLMON: Interpersonal.

27:23.667 --> 27:27.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I said something you
didn't agree with, you
responded negatively, it
ended up in gun violence.

27:29.867 --> 27:34.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Violence interrupter
Ulysses "U.S." Floyd was a
leader in one of Chicago's most

27:34.700 --> 27:37.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
notorious gangs, the
Gangster Disciples.

27:37.333 --> 27:38.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ULYSSES "U.S." FLOYD, Violence
Interrupter: I know I helped
start this mess, so I wanted

27:38.333 --> 27:41.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to help clean it up.

27:41.133 --> 27:46.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: He told us that
gangs are very different now
than they were in his day.

27:47.600 --> 27:49.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ULYSSES "U.S." FLOYD: One or
two men control everything.

27:49.300 --> 27:52.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Now you have got a lot
of different little
gangs split all over.

27:52.900 --> 27:56.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are offsprings of the major
gangs, what they call cliques.

27:56.000 --> 27:58.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And they just do
what they want to do.

27:58.667 --> 28:00.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ain't nobody really in control,
no structure, no rules.

28:00.933 --> 28:05.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The number of
neighborhoods where Chicago's
branch of Cure Violence operates

28:05.167 --> 28:07.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
varies based on funding.

28:07.333 --> 28:11.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But a Justice Department study
found that, at one point, the
group helped reduce violence

28:11.967 --> 28:16.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by 40 percent to 70 percent
in some of the areas
where they were operating.

28:18.367 --> 28:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Today, they are in only five
of the city's 77 neighborhoods.

