cultural figures.

35:00.700 --> 35:01.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Wham!, as Angus Walker
described in his report there,
were -- they were almost the

35:01.967 --> 35:03.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
harbingers, the heralds
of Thatcherism himself.

35:03.933 --> 35:05.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The group was very
anti-Thatcher, famously
anti-Thatcher, but
their brand of pop and

35:05.933 --> 35:08.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the kind of aspiration and
the brightness of that pop
was radical and revolutionary.

35:08.067 --> 35:10.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Britain, at that point in
the early '80s, emerging from
a period of sort of late '70s

35:12.267 --> 35:15.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
